-- CTC Media’s TV Weekly Audience Falls in Russia, TNS-Global Says
-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 2012-09-27T17:30:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-27/ctc-media-s-tv-weekly-audience-falls-in-russia-tns-global-says.html
CTC Media Inc. (CTCM) ’s CTC television
channel saw its average daily share of Russian viewers fall in
the week to Sept. 23, according to TNS-Global.  The share of Russian viewers aged 18 years and older for
CTC TV, the Nasdaq-listed Russian media company’s biggest source
of revenue, shrunk to 5.7 percent in the week to Sept. 23 from
6.1 percent the previous week, TNS-Global said by e-mail today.
CTC was the sixth most-watched TV channel in the week to Sept.
23, from fifth a week earlier.  CTC’s average daily audience among viewers 4 years old and
over fell to 6.5 percent in the week to Sept. 23 from 7 percent
in the previous week, the data show. CTC remained the fifth
most-watched TV channel among viewers 4 year and over in the
week to Sept. 23, the researcher said.  Russia’s Rossiya-1, NTV Television, Pervyi Kanal and TNT TV
were the top four channels in both age categories, the data
show. Fifth Channel was the fifth-most watched among viewers 18
years and older.  To contact the reporters on this story:
